			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Position: Product/Project Manager<br />
	Full time (Start Up hours). Location: San Francisco, Downtown.</p>
<p>
	Company Overview: BringIt (www.BringIt.com) is an innovative, new and unique platform that allows any gaming publisher to add challenges and competitions to their current user experience, enabling them to increase monetization and user engagement. BringIt is currently focused on the social gaming space and is working with industry leaders including Crowdstar and RockYou! We are looking to expand our current team to support new product and partnership rollouts. If you want to make an ENORMOUS impact on the strategic development of an innovative new player in the world of gaming, bring it!</p>
<p>
	Overview: The Product/Project Manager will be a results-oriented, and experienced senior leader who will be responsible for adding to and organizing BringIt&rsquo;s product strategy. Candidates should have visionary product insight, combined with strong organizational, leadership, and business skills. The Product/Project Manager combines a great instinct for developing compelling products with a strong focus on partner and end user engagement. The ideal candidate will have the technical aptitude to work with the engineering team, as well as the business acumen to drive product goals and strategies.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Responsibilities:<br />
	&bull; Coordinate deliverables with dependent teams, and 3rd-party partners<br />
	&bull; Ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment, with minimal guidance<br />
	&bull; Lead usability and design efforts to build highly intuitive, and engaging user interfaces<br />
	&bull; Apply user-centered design principles to define user personas, construct wire-frames, and build interactive prototypes<br />
	&bull; Work with product, design, and marketing teams to advance the product roadmap<br />
	&bull; Define and coordinate in-person usability testing, site wide a/b testing, and other user experience research<br />
	&bull; Extract, analyze, interpret, and summarize data from various sources<br />
	&bull; Additional product support, including customer inquiries and other product operations</p>
<p>
	Requirements:<br />
	&bull; 3-5 years of Product/Project management experience in a fast-paced environment<br />
	&bull; Ability to work in a technical software development environment, and understand technical issues/requirements<br />
	&bull; Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br />
	&bull; Proven track record of working closely with the engineering, QA, and operations team through the full project lifecycle<br />
	&bull; Significant people and organizational management skills. A natural leader and mentor<br />
	&bull; Graduate degree is a plus</p>
<p>
	<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
